The '''Republic escape pod'''<ref name="Concept Art Gallery" /> was a type of [[escape pod]] used by the [[Galactic Republic]] during the [[Clone Wars]].<ref name="Ambush" /> In [[22 BBY]],<ref name="Timelines">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]''</ref> [[Jedi Master]] [[Yoda]] and [[clone trooper]]s [[Thire]], [[Jek]], and [[Rys]] used a Republic escape pod to land on [[Rugosa]] where the Jedi Master had a meeting with the [[Toydarian]] [[King]] [[Katuunko]].<ref name="Ambush" />

In the same year,<ref name="Timelines" /> [[Kel Dor]] [[Jedi]] Master [[Plo Koon]] and clone troopers [[Wolffe]], [[Sinker]], and [[Boost]] survived an attacked by the ''[[Malevolence]]'' in a Republic escape pod after their [[Venator-class Star Destroyer]] ''[[Triumphant]]'' was destroyed.<ref name="Rising Malevolence">{{TCW|Rising Malevolence|Rising ''Malevolence''}}</ref>

{{Veh-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The Republic escape pod first appeared in "[[Ambush]],"<ref name="Ambush" /> the first episode of the animated television series ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' [[The Clone Wars: Season One|first season]], which originally aired on [[October 3]], [[2008]].<ref name="Ambush EG">{{SW|url=series/clone-wars/ambush-episode-guide|text="Ambush" Episode Guide &#124; The Clone Wars}}</ref> The pod was first identified as a Republic escape pod in Ambush's episode guide's concept art gallery on [[StarWars.com]].<ref name="Concept Art Gallery" />

